Saturday’s launch was a test sat – the ~8x larger production version, Bluebird1 (BB1), which is needed to deliver the service and financials $ASTS has promised, is two years late and our checks point to further costly delays ahead (3/8)

Skepticism from the space and satcom experts we interviewed surrounds nearly every aspect of AST’s plan: spacecraft design, quality of service, addressable market, and ability to execute against competition from SpaceX and Apple (2/8)

$MRTX G12C inhibitor is a failure, stock -34%. On duration of response and toxicity, the latest data strongly confirms adagrasib's inferiority to Amgen's Lumakras. Sad news for patients, but hard to imagine Mirati getting any traction on adagrasib after this https://t.co/T73bwEgHv9

$DWAC’s ability to close its merger with TMTG is threatened along two distinct but inextricably linked regulatory paths: the need for an effective S-4 regarding the proposed merger, and the active SEC investigation into material misstatements contained in $DWAC’s S-1. (4/9)

The SEC has been handed a prime opp to send a message to the industry. Not only is $DWAC and TMTG high-profile, but the deal involves a repeat offender. $DWAC’s sponsor is an obscure Chinese firm that has seen three of its shell companies killed by the SEC in the past. (3/9)
